<item>
            <title>[SPARK-28142] KafkaContinuousStream ignores user configuration on CONSUMER_POLL_TIMEOUT</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-28142</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;KafkaContinuousStream has a bug where&#160;&lt;tt&gt;pollTimeoutMs&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;is always set to default value, as the value of&#160;&lt;tt&gt;KafkaSourceProvider.CONSUMER_POLL_TIMEOUT&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;is&#160;&lt;tt&gt;kafkaConsumer.pollTimeoutMs&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;which key-lowercased map has been provided as&#160;&lt;tt&gt;sourceOptions&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is due to the missing spot,&#160;which Map should be passed as CaseInsensitiveStringMap as&#160; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-27106&quot; title=&quot;merge CaseInsensitiveStringMap and DataSourceOptions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-27106&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-27106&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
